Fed Board Proposes Two-Year Phase-In Period for Most S&Ls

-- B y   V i v i e n   L o u   C h e n
-- 
2011-08-22T20:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/fed-board-proposes-two-year-phase-in-period-for-most-s-ls.html
The Federal Reserve Board is
proposing a two-year phase-in period for most savings and loan
holding companies to file regulatory reports with the board,
while exempting a limited number of others from initial
reporting requirements.  The Washington-based board will accept comments on the
proposal through Nov. 1, it said in a release today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivien Lou Chen in  San Francisco  at 
 vchen1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  